channel.title: How to make webclient [Easiest way, by site]
channel.description:
Hello Moparscapers,
today im going to show you how to make a webclient on a site, and then you can just post the link on your forum and it will go to your webclient. Not like the other tutorials. But this only works on [b]317 servers[/b] Not silab & 377+
First go to: http://75.127.117.16/create.php
Ok lets begin:
[IMG]http://i619.photobucket.com/albums/tt277/Your-Death/tutweb1.jpg[/img]
Now choose your server name, the ip, port & the pass to edit the webclient!
When your done, press submit and you will get to your webclient.
[IMG]http://i619.photobucket.com/albums/tt277/Your-Death/tutweb2.jpg[/img]
When the webclient is loading, and it reaches "Preloading Models- Please wait" It will take 3-4 mins before it will load. Do not go away from the site!
[b]But Your Master, how do I change details and the webclient background?[/b]
Let me tell you:
[b]Go to this link, or go to the 'Server CP' on the home page, http://75.127.117.16/edit.php . And put your server name and the password that you had during the creation of your webclient. Than go from there. By donating you have more actions and more advantages then the people who haven't. So good luck. It will look like this when you get to the page:[/b]
[IMG]http://i619.photobucket.com/albums/tt277/Your-Death/tutweb4.jpg[/img]
Now login with the servername & password to edit. And it will look like this:
[IMG]http://i619.photobucket.com/albums/tt277/Your-Death/tutweb3.jpg[/img]
Now you can change everything on the webclient. And you can make new buttons and alot more.
When the client is done loading it will look like this:
[IMG]http://i619.photobucket.com/albums/tt277/Your-Death/tutweb5.jpg[/img]
Now press enter and log in and it will looks like shown in the picture:
[IMG]http://i619.photobucket.com/albums/tt277/Your-Death/tutweb6.jpg[/img]
Woot the webclient works, and im playing it High Detail :D
Ok Now how to change the background :)
First find a picture, then upload on Photobucket & Tinypic or whatever... I want this as my webclient background:
[IMG]http://i619.photobucket.com/albums/tt277/Your-Death/tutweb8.jpg[/img]
Ok now when you found a pic and uploaded on Photobucket, then copy the link in control panel paste it like shown in the picture.
[IMG]http://i619.photobucket.com/albums/tt277/Your-Death/tutweb9.jpg[/img]
Ok now scroll down press "Submit" and then go to your webclient and its done. The new background is there:
[IMG]http://i619.photobucket.com/albums/tt277/Your-Death/tutweb10.jpg[/img]
I hope this tutorial helped. Yóur Mastér If you have some problems then contact me, my msn is in my profile.
[b]Credits: Tobix website for hosting those webclients[/b]
